  <Subject Subject_ID="300107620">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300107604</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>Cypriote pottery styles [300107604], Cypriote styles [300107592], Cypriote [300020627], Near Eastern (Early Western World) [300019571], Early Western World [300019255], styles, periods, and cultures by region [300111079], Styles and Periods (hierarchy name) [300015646], Styles and Periods Facet [300264088]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the pottery style found in Cyprus from the Early Cypriote period beginning around 2300 BCE through the Geometric period ending around 750 BCE. While the style underwent changes over time, generally it is characterized by pottery decorated with dark paint on a white or light background.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo de cerámica encontrado en Chipre a partir del período Chipriota Temprano que empieza alrededor del 2300 a.C. hasta el final del período Geométrico que finaliza alrededor del 750 a.C. Aunque el estilo sufrió muchos cambios con el tiempo, generalmente se caracteriza por cerámica decorada con pintura oscura en un fondo blanco o claro.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de aardewerkstijl die werd gevonden op Cyprus, van de Vroeg-Cypriotische periode die begon rond 2.300 v. Chr. tot aan de Geometrische periode die eindigde rond 750 v. Chr. Hoewel de stijl in de loop der tijd veranderingen onderging, kenmerkt deze zich in het algemeen door met donkere verf op een witte of lichte achtergrond gedecoreerd aardewerk.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指在賽普勒斯島上發展，始於約末西元前2300年的賽普勒斯時代早期，直至結束於西元前750年前後的幾何時代（Geometric period）之陶器風格。雖然這個風格隨著時間演變而歷經迭變，但一般而言，其特色是以白色或淡色為底，繪上深色裝飾圖案的陶器。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
